irissync is a standalone binary that owns the IRIS source boundary in both
directions: it liberates IRIS routine source to the filesystem (materialize
routine source → mirror + manifest) and writes edited routines back (`push`).
The read verbs (list/pull/status/verify) never write to IRIS; `push` is the
opt-in write path and the SOLE DB WRITER, gated by a single-writer lock + a
manifest conflict-check + detect-and-defer so it never clobbers a change made
underneath it (the lock is the safety mechanism — see
liberation-binary-design.md §5). It was scaffolded from go-cli-template. Go
binaries built from it are Apache-2.0 (per-tier license split — see
host-side-go-toolchain-adr.md §3.2).
